# Sprint 8: The Home Base (Dashboard) - Complete 🎉

I've completed all tasks for Sprint 8. Here's a breakdown of what was accomplished:

## 1. Dashboard Component Created
I created a new React component at `frontend/src/components/Dashboard.tsx`. This component handles:
- Fetching and displaying the list of tracked applications from the backend (`GET /api/applications`).
- A form to add a new job application (`POST /api/applications`).
- Functionality to edit an existing application (`PUT /api/applications/{id}`).
- Functionality to delete an application (`DELETE /api/applications/{id}`).
- The dashboard is styled consistently with the rest of the app (dark mode, glowing borders).

## 2. Integrated into App.tsx
I imported the new `Dashboard` component into `App.tsx` and placed it at the bottom of the page, acting as the "Home Base" for the job search tracking as requested in the sprint definition.

## 3. Backend Verification
The required backend components (Data Model and CRUD endpoints) were already present in `JobApplication.java` and `JobApplicationController.java`, so no additional backend work was necessary. They seamlessly integrated with the new frontend dashboard.

## 4. Checklist Updated
I updated the `checklist_advanced.md` file, marking all tasks in Sprint 8 as completed `[x]`.

## Next Steps
You can now start tracking your job applications directly from the app! To verify the changes, make sure your backend server is running and interact with the new dashboard section at the bottom of the application. 

